  "prompt": "How good is DTU?",
  "response": "The Technical University of Denmark (DTU) is highly regarded both nationally and internationally for its excellence in engineering, technology, and scientific research. Here are some key points that illustrate the quality and reputation of DTU:\n\n1. **Academic Excellence**: DTU consistently ranks among the top universities in the world for engineering and technology. It is known for its rigorous academic programs and high standards of education.\n\n2. **Research Output**: DTU is renowned for its strong research output, particularly in fields such as environmental engineering, biotechnology, and computer science. The university collaborates with industry and other academic institutions globally to drive innovation and technological advancements.\n\n3. **Industry Connections**: DTU has robust ties with industry, providing students with ample opportunities for internships, collaborations, and real-world experience. This helps students apply theoretical knowledge in practical settings and enhances their employability.\n\n4. **Facilities and Resources**: DTU offers state-of-the-art facilities, laboratories, and research centers equipped with the latest technologies. These resources support students and faculty in conducting cutting-edge research and projects.\n\n5. **International Environment**: DTU attracts a diverse body of students and researchers from around the world, fostering a cosmopolitan and global learning environment. English-taught programs and international partnerships further contribute to its international appeal.\n\n6. **Sustainability Focus**: DTU places a strong emphasis on sustainability and environmental issues, integrating these themes into its research, education, and campus initiatives.\n\nOverall, DTU is considered one of the leading technical universities globally and is an excellent choice for students seeking a high-quality education in engineering and technology fields.",
